/F1 18 Tf
(Transit Alert Lifecycle Manager) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(Abhishek Wabale - Product Case Study) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(CONTEXT) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Transit agencies manage critical information such as service alerts, routes, schedules,) Tj
T*
(  stops, and disruptions.) Tj
T*
(- Riders depend on timely and reliable service information to plan trips and avoid) Tj
T*
(  surprises.) Tj
T*
(- The product opportunity is to help agencies maintain alert quality throughout the full) Tj
T*
(  lifecycle, not just create alerts faster.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(PROBLEM) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Transit agencies experience operational complexity when managing service alerts) Tj
T*
(  manually.) Tj
T*
(- The alert lifecycle - creation, publishing, monitoring, updating, extending, and closing) Tj
T*
(  - depends heavily on staff follow-up.) Tj
T*
(- As alert volume grows, teams can miss alerts that need review, alerts nearing) Tj
T*
(  expiration, or alerts that should already be closed.) Tj
T*
(- Outdated rider-facing information can reduce trust and create confusion for daily) Tj
T*
(  commuters.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(USERS) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Agency communications officer: creates and updates alerts under time pressure and is) Tj
T*
(  accountable for accuracy.) Tj
T*
(- Daily rider: checks transit information before leaving and expects the service status to) Tj
T*
(  be current.) Tj
T*
(- Account manager: supports agencies after onboarding and needs the product to be simple) Tj
T*
(  and scalable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(WHY THIS FEATURE WON) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Alert Lifecycle Manager ranked highest in RICE because it directly solves the core) Tj
T*
(  lifecycle maintenance problem.) Tj
T*
(- It scored higher than an AI alert-writing assistant because the main issue was not only) Tj
T*
(  creating alerts; it was keeping already-published alerts accurate.) Tj
T*
(- It scored higher than an insights dashboard because it gives staff an action queue, not) Tj
T*
(  only reporting.) Tj
T*
(- The feature helps staff identify which alerts require review, update, extension, or) Tj
T*
(  closure before riders encounter stale information.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(SOLUTION) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- The feature provides a centralized review queue for active alerts.) Tj
T*
(- It highlights alerts that are healthy, need review, are expiring soon, or may be) Tj
T*
ET
