(  outdated.) Tj
T*
(- Staff can quickly review, update, extend, or close alerts from one workflow.) Tj
T*
(- The experience reduces manual monitoring and improves rider-facing information quality.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(SUCCESS METRICS) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- North Star Metric: percentage of active alerts that remain accurate and up to date) Tj
T*
(  throughout their lifecycle.) Tj
T*
(- Initiative Metric: percentage of alerts reviewed, updated, or closed before becoming) Tj
T*
(  outdated.) Tj
T*
(- Reduce outdated active alerts by 50%.) Tj
T*
(- Increase alerts reviewed before expiration from 40% to 80%.) Tj
T*
(- Reduce rider complaints related to inaccurate service alerts.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(IMPACT) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Improves information accuracy by surfacing alerts requiring attention.) Tj
T*
(- Improves operational efficiency by reducing manual monitoring effort.) Tj
T*
(- Improves scalability as alert volume grows.) Tj
T*
(- Improves rider experience by keeping service information current and trustworthy.) Tj
T*
(- Expands product value from alert creation to alert quality management.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(ROLLOUT) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- Pilot with 2-3 existing transit agencies and monitor alert review rates.) Tj
T*
(- Move to general availability with onboarding guides and product walkthroughs.) Tj
T*
(- Optimize with smart recommendations, alert analytics, collaboration workflows, and) Tj
T*
(  expanded reporting.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
/F1 13 Tf
(WHAT I LEARNED) Tj
T*
/F1 11 Tf
(- The highest-impact opportunity is not always the most visible feature.) Tj
T*
(- Activity metrics such as number of alerts created are weaker than outcome metrics such) Tj
T*
(  as lifecycle accuracy.) Tj
T*
(- A strong operational product should reduce hidden manual work while improving the user-) Tj
T*
(  facing experience.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
